<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn222">  222  The tailor's daughter is clearly ALP and is not, as some commentators have suggested, her own daughter Issy. What we have here is yet another version of how ALP and HCE came to be married. In corroboration of this view, when in Book IV as she prepares for her death ALP recalls the occasion of their first meeting, she says &lsquo;I was but teen, a tiler's dot&rsquo; (a tailor's daughter). See <a name="n50173a" href="../fnbs/n50all.htm#n50173a">N50 (VI.B.37):173(a)</a>.  </div>
